              rec_mode - recording mode (K4 drives)

Syntax:     rec_mode=bw,bits,chan

Response:   rec_mode/bw,bits,chan,form,ts,im,nm,ta,pb


Settable Parameters:
bw    overall recording bandwidth in MHz, 64 (default) , 128, or
      256
bits    number of bits per sample: 1 (default), 2, 4, or 8
chan  channels recorded: 1, 2, 4, 8, or 16 (default)

Monitor-only parameters: 
form  recording format: OLD or NEW
ts    time stamp: ON or OFF
im    insertion mode for time stamp: FB (fixed bit) or FT (fixed
      time)
nm    insertion number: 0 to 30
ta    TAP setting mode: 0 or 1
pb    pass-band setting: 0 to 16

Comments:
This command is only for DFC2100. This command sets the recording
mode and may require up to 17 seconds to be completed due to
digital filter set-up.
